{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778536876,"nonce":"i7vPPGIcpTHU23Qs7pGQ0bz0rIA=","message":"## Smoothness weight correction (from prior matrix `2bc95fd`)\n\nThe prior 6-cell anti-anticipation matrix used `nn_hidden_derivative = 1e2`. Re-reading Shahbazi 2025 Eq. 1, the effective derivative weight is `1e-5 Г— 1e2 = 1e-3` (outer Г— inner). So our `1e2` direct weight was 1e5Г— Shahbazi-effective. Variance-collapse and accelerated-reach effects in that matrix reflect aggressive smoothness, not literature-faithful settings. See follow-up comment on `2bc95fd` for the full correction note.\n\n## Direct loss-function comparison\n\n| Term | C\u0026S 2019 | Shahbazi 2025 | rlrmp **intended** (next matrix) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Position-error norm | L2 quadratic (x^T Q x) | L1 | L2 (squared) |\n| Position target during hold | origin (= start) | start | start (`effector_hold_pos`) |\n| Position target during reach | reach target | goal | goal (`effector_pos_running`) |\n| Time weighting on position | (t/N)^6 back-loaded | uniform | uniform (`hold_pos = pos_running` equal); back-loaded variants tested in `f47abb1` |\n| Position outer weight | Q diag = [10^6, 10^6, 10^5, 10^5, 1, 1] terminal | 10^3 (uniform) | 10.0 (both terms; equal) |\n| Late-window position ramp | subsumed by (t/N)^6 | none | NONE (`effector_pos_late` = 0) |\n| Velocity-zero hold penalty | subsumed by Q | none | NONE (`effector_hold_vel` = 0) |\n| Late-window velocity ramp | n/a | none | NONE (`effector_vel_late` = 0) |\n| Final-velocity penalty | implicit (terminal Q) | none | NONE (`effector_final_vel` = 0) |\n| Endpoint jerk | none | вЂ–бє‹М‡М‡вЂ–ВІ Г— 10^5 | `nn_output_jerk` = 1e5 (or 0 in no-jerk cells) |\n| Controller-force magnitude | вЂ–uвЂ–ВІ (L2) | n/a (uses muscle layer) | `nn_output` = 1e-5 |\n| Muscle-force magnitude | n/a (no muscles) | f^T f Г— 10^-1 outer | n/a (no muscles) |\n| Muscle force-derivative | n/a | 3e-3 Г— 10^-1 outer = 3e-4 effective | n/a |\n| Hidden-state magnitude | n/a | 10^-5 effective | `nn_hidden` = 1e-5 |\n| Hidden-state derivative | n/a | 10^-3 effective (10^-5 outer Г— 10^2 inner) | `nn_hidden_derivative` = **1e-3** |\n| Catch trials | n/a (analytical) | p = 0.5 | p = 0.5 |\n| Pre-go motor mask | n/a | none | NONE (`nn_output_pre_go` = 0) |\n| Pre-go hidden-deriv mask | n/a | none | NONE (`nn_hidden_derivative_pre_go` = 0) |\n\n**Notes**:\n- rlrmp's `nn_output_jerk` operates on `effector.vel` вЂ” second-difference yields endpoint jerk, matching Shahbazi's `L_j`. Name is misleading.\n- Adversarial training (linear_dynamics adversary) is excluded вЂ” that's a training-method axis (trial distribution), not a loss term.\n- rlrmp prunes zero-weighted terms at build time (`loss.py:641,649,674` etc.) вЂ” setting a weight to 0 removes the term from the graph entirely.\n- L2 (rlrmp) vs L1 (Shahbazi) decision documented in proposal `_artifacts/scratchpad/literature_replication_proposal.md` В§2.5. Choice: L2 (matches C\u0026S analytical framework, which is the project's analytical anchor).\n\n## Next-step issues\n\n- **`f47abb1`** (`feature`, `run`) вЂ” Lit-replication 6-cell matrix. Tests jerk on/off Г— position shape (flat / (t/N)^6 post-go / (t/N)^6 throughout) at corrected smoothness weight. **This is the immediate next run.**\n- **`9a82e55`** (`feature`) вЂ” Position-weight + target_ratio sweeps. Deferred, executed only if 6-cell results suggest miscalibration.\n- **`cea2e62`** (`feature`, on `4d38c15`) вЂ” Analytical bridge for rlrmp cost (no-jerk variant). Parallel analysis to compare trained no-jerk networks against an LQR/Riccati derivation for our exact cost structure.\n- **`2e1a6ad`** (`feature`) вЂ” Power-law schedule support in `make_late_discount_from_epoch`. Prerequisite for the 6-cell matrix's (t/N)^6 cells.","files":null}]}